# Docker build context exclusions.
#
# The Dockerfile uses surgical `COPY <path> <dest>` lines (no `COPY . .`),
# but the daemon still tarballs the entire build context up front and
# applies these patterns. Keeping the context tight makes the transfer
# fast (especially when the daemon is remote, like Depot/buildx).
#
# Strategy:
#   1. Exclude obvious noise (node_modules, dist, caches, logs, etc.)
#   2. Exclude documentation/metadata that compilation never reads (the
#      Kikobeats/untracked autogen would emit these as a baseline).
#   3. Re-include anything the build stage actually COPYs.

# ─── Build artifacts (re-installed/regenerated inside the image) ───────────
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/out/
**/coverage/
**/coverage-isolated/
**/.cache/
**/.ccache/

# ─── Git, CI, IDE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.github/
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml

# ─── Tests + fixtures (not needed in the runtime image) ────────────────────
test/
tests/
__tests__/
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.mts
**/*.test.js
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.mts
**/*.spec.js

# ─── Docs + metadata (compilation never reads these) ───────────────────────
docs/
**/*.md
**/*.MD
**/*.markdown
**/AUTHOR
**/AUTHORS
**/CHANGELOG
**/CONTRIBUTING
**/CONTRIBUTORS
**/HISTORY
**/MAINTAINERS
**/NEWS
**/NOTICE
**/SECURITY
**/SUPPORT
**/COPYING
**/CREDITS

# ─── Source maps + type-only artifacts (not bundled) ───────────────────────
**/*.map
**/*.map.json
**/*.flow

# ─── Lint / format / CI configs ────────────────────────────────────────────
.editorconfig
.prettierrc*
.eslintrc*
.stylelintrc*
**/appveyor.yml
**/.travis.yml
**/circle.yml
**/.circleci/

# ─── Logs + temp files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
**/*.log
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ─── Secrets + local-only state ────────────────────────────────────────────
**/.env*
**/.npm
**/.config
**/.scannerwork
**/certs
**/nodemon.json
**/.dtx
.gitignore

# ─── Repo-only directories the runtime doesn't need ────────────────────────
hooks/
mock-client/
reports/
docs/
.claude/
# Re-include .claude/hooks because pnpm install resolves them as workspace
# packages (declared in pnpm-workspace.yaml `packages:`).
!.claude/
!.claude/hooks/
!.claude/hooks/**

# Brand assets (PNGs)
*.png

# ─── Re-includes for files the Dockerfile DOES COPY ────────────────────────
!package.json
!pnpm-lock.yaml
!pnpm-workspace.yaml
!index.ts
!lib/**
!scripts/**
!tsconfig.json
!tsconfig.dts.json
